
Problem 1: "Not Loaded" is Unacceptable
A monitoring dashboard that opens to "Not loaded" on every metric is dead on arrival. Nobody will trust it or come back. The design principle should be:

Every page must show SOMETHING within 3 seconds of opening, even without marts.

Recommendation:

Current Behavior	Should Be
Shell pages query mart → mart missing → "Not loaded"	Shell pages query ACCOUNT_USAGE directly with a 24h bounded window
User must click "Load Investigation Detail"	Page auto-loads the top 5 KPIs on open (bounded, cheap queries)
Mart is a prerequisite	Mart is an accelerator (faster/richer), not a gate
The DBA Control Room shell should on first paint:

Run 3 cheap queries (credits 24h, failed queries 24h, failed tasks 24h) against ACCOUNT_USAGE directly
Show those numbers immediately
THEN offer "Load Full Detail" for the expensive stuff
Problem 2: Visual Design Recommendations
What's wrong with the current layout:
Too many empty cards — 9 signal lanes all showing "Not loaded" is visual noise. Don't render cards you can't fill.
No clear hierarchy — Everything is the same size, same style. The eye doesn't know where to go first.
Too much chrome, not enough data — "DBA Command Board" heading, "Data freshness" box, "Snapshot is company-level" caption, "DBA Control Room shows cached triage..." text — that's 4 lines of meta-information before any actual data.
The signal lane board is the wrong component — Small cards with label/state/value work great when filled with data. They're terrible when empty. They look broken.
